Decimal number to binary in java using recursion

[Decimal number to binary in java using recursion](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/decimal-number-to-binary-in-java-using-recursion/)

Hereâ€™s the program to convert decimal to binary using recursion. The logic to convert decimal to binary using recursion is,

if(decimal == 0)
return 0;
else
return(decimal % 2 + 10 * toBinary(decimal / 2));

public class DecimalToBinaryUsingRecursion
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      int inputDecimal = 50;
      System.out.println(toBinary(inputDecimal));
   }
   static int toBinary(int decimal)
   {
      if(decimal == 0)
         return 0;
      else
         return(decimal % 2 + 10 * toBinary(decimal / 2));
   }
}
